# Jonnovative Design System Rules

## Token Usage — No Hardcoded Values

All colors, spacing, typography, shadows, and radii MUST use CSS custom properties from `@jonnovative/tokens`.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — hardcoded values
<div style={{ color: '#2563EB', padding: '16px' }}>

// ✅ GOOD — CSS Modules with token variables
<div className={styles.card}>
```

```css
/* ❌ BAD */
.card { color: #2563EB; padding: 16px; }

/* ✅ GOOD */
.card { color: var(--color-primary-600); padding: var(--space-4); }
```

## No Inline Styles

Never use the `style=` JSX attribute. All styling goes in `.module.css` files.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<button style={{ backgroundColor: 'blue' }}>

// ✅ GOOD
<button className={styles.button}>
```

## No `any` Types

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
function process(data: any) {}

// ✅ GOOD
function process(data: Record<string, unknown>) {}
```

## Component API Requirements

Every component in `packages/ui` MUST:
- Export a fully typed `Props` interface
- Accept `className` for extension
- Accept `data-testid` for testing
- Have a companion `.stories.tsx`, `.test.tsx`, and `.a11y.test.tsx`

```tsx
// ✅ Correct shape
export interface ButtonProps extends ButtonHTMLAttributes<HTMLButtonElement> {
  variant?: 'primary' | 'secondary';
  'data-testid'?: string;
}
```

## No Business Logic in `packages/ui`

The UI package must stay framework-agnostic. Never add:
- API calls / fetch
- React Router / navigation side-effects
- Global state (Zustand, Redux, Context that holds server data)
- Authentication checks

## Import Rules for App Packages

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — importing from internal paths
import { Button } from '../../packages/ui/src/components/Button';

// ✅ GOOD — always use the package name
import { Button } from '@jonnovative/ui';
```

## Atomic Structure

Follow the strict three-tier hierarchy:
1. `primitives/` — Box, Text, Stack, Container (no business meaning)
2. `components/` — Button, Card, Input (UI semantics, no domain logic)
3. `patterns/` — Navigation, PricingCard, Footer (composed, page-level)

Never import from a higher tier into a lower tier.
